ition\n\nLet me be more specific. This is a 1,2-nucleophilic addition to an electrophilic C=C bond (in a cyanine dye system). The nucleophile (hydrazine) attacks the β-carbon of the conjugated system.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the atom mapping and bond changes:\n\nThe key transformation at the reaction center:\n- C:21=C:20 → C:21-C:20 (double bond to single bond)\n- C:20 gains NH2+:10-NH:61-CH3 substituent\n- N+:23 → N:23 (charge neutralization)\n\nThis is nucleophilic addition (1,2-addition) of hydrazine to the electrophilic alkene of the cyanine dye.\n\nMechanistic class: nucleophilic_addition\n\nReaction center: C:21=C:20 bond with addition of :NH2:10-:NH:61 to C:20, and N+:23 → N:23"
