=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Looking at the mapped reaction, I need to identify the mechanistic class and reaction center.

**Key observations from atom mapping:**
- C:21=C:20 double bond in the cyanine dye is broken → becomes C:21–C:20 single bond
- N⁺:23 loses its positive charge → becomes neutral N:23
- Hydrazine (NH2:10–NH:61–CH3) adds to C:20, with NH2:10 becoming NH2⁺ (charge transferred from N⁺:23)
- The nucleophile attacks the electrophilic vinyl carbon (C:20) of the polymethine chain

**Mechanistic class:** This is a **1,2-nucleophilic addition** of hydrazine to the electrophilic C=C bond of the cyanine dye. The nucleophile adds across the C:21=C:20 bond, with the positive charge migrating from the ring nitrogen (N⁺:23) to the incoming amine (NH2⁺:10).

nucleophilic_addition

